<body>
<p>
Let \(T:V\to W\) be a
<a knowl="defs/vec/map">linear map</a>.
</p>
<p>
The <b>image</b> of \(T\), denoted \(T(V)\),
is the set of all \(Tv\in W\).
</p>
<ul>
<li>
This forms a subspace of \(W\).
<details>
<summary>
[explanation]
</summary>
Let \(\alpha,\beta\in\mathbf F\) and \(Tu, Tv\in T(V)\).
Then \(u, v\in V\), hence \(\alpha u + \beta v\in V\),
hence \(T(\alpha u + \beta v)\in T(V)\).
</details>
</li>
<li>
A map \(T\) is surjective if and only if \(T(V) = W\).
</li>
</ul>
</body>
</html>
